President Cyril Ramaphosa has expressed sadness following the death of 24 people in a head-on collision between a mini-bus taxi and a bus near Giyani in Limpopo. The victims were travelling home after attending the Youth Day celebrations in Sekgosese when the accident occurred on Sunday night. “President Ramaphosa has expressed deep sadness at the passing away of twenty four people following a collision between a mini bus taxi and a bus. The president has said that the nation is heartbroken. It is devastating to lose so many young lives at the time we expected so much of them when they were in the prime of their lives,” says Ramaphosa’ spokesperson, Khusela Diko.  WATCH: R81 accident in Limpopo claims 24 lives  